fields.name: Dark Side Of The Moon
fields.description: The Dark Side of the Moon is the eighth studio album by the English rock band Pink Floyd, released on 1 March 1973 by Harvest Records in the UK and Capitol Records in the US.

fields.name: Is This It
fields.description: Is This It is the debut studio album by American band the Strokes

fields.name: The Clash
fields.description: The Clash is the debut studio album by English punk rock band, The Clash. It was released on 8 April 1977 through CBS Records

fields.name: Helplessness Blues
fields.description: Helplessness Blues is the second studio album by American band Fleet Foxes, released on May 3, 2011, by Sub Pop and Bella Union. The album received universal acclaim from critics, going on to be nominated for Best Folk Album at the 54th Annual Grammy Awards.

fields.name: Music For the Jilted generation
fields.description: Music for the Jilted Generation is the second studio album by English electronic music group the Prodigy. It was first released in 4 July 1994 by XL Recordings in the United Kingdom and by Mute Records in the United States.

fields.name: Renaissance
fields.description: Renaissance is the seventh studio album by American singer Beyoncé, released on July 29, 2022, by Parkwood Entertainment and Columbia Records.

fields.name: Red Headed Stranger
fields.description: Red Headed Stranger is the eighteenth studio album by American outlaw country singer Willie Nelson, released in 1975.

fields.name: A love Supreme
fields.description: A Love Supreme is an album by American jazz saxophonist John Coltrane. He recorded it in one session on December 9, 1964 at Van Gelder Studio in Englewood Cliffs, New Jersey, leading a quartet featuring pianist McCoy Tyner, bassist Jimmy Garrison and drummer Elvin Jones.

fields.name: Songs In The Key Of Life
fields.description: Songs in the Key of Life is the eighteenth studio album by American singer, songwriter and musician Stevie Wonder. A double album, it was released on September 28, 1976, by Tamla Records, a division of Motown.

fields.name: Bach: The Goldberg Variations
fields.description: Bach: The Goldberg Variations is the debut album of Canadian classical pianist Glenn Gould. An interpretation of Johann Sebastian Bach's Goldberg Variations, the 1956 record launched Gould's career as a renowned international pianist, and became one of the most well-known piano recordings

fields.name: Enter the Wu-Tang (36 Chambers)
fields.description: Enter the Wu-Tang (36 Chambers) is the debut studio album by the American hip-hop group Wu-Tang Clan, released on November 9, 1993, by BMG, RCA Records and Loud Records. Recording sessions took place during late 1992 to early 1993 at Firehouse Studio in New York City.

fields.name: Buena Vista Social Club
fields.description: Buena Vista Social Club is the debut album by the Buena Vista Social Club, an ensemble of Cuban musicians directed by Juan de Marcos González

fields.name: The West Side Story
fields.description: West Side Story is the soundtrack album to the 1961 film West Side Story, featuring music by Leonard Bernstein and lyrics by Stephen Sondheim.

fields.name: Catch A Fire
fields.description: Catch a Fire is the fifth studio album by the reggae band The Wailers, released in April 1973. It was their first album released by Island Records.

fields.name: The Real Folk Blues
fields.description: The Real Folk Blues is an album by blues musician John Lee Hooker that was recorded in Chicago in 1966 and released by the Chess label.

fields.name: The Rising Of The Moon: Irish Songs of Rebellion
fields.description: The Rising of the Moon: Irish Songs of Rebellion is a collection of traditional Irish folk songs performed by The Clancy Brothers and Tommy Makem. It was the group's first album and was initially recorded in 1956

fields.name: DENON DP-29F Belt Drive Turntable - Silver
fields.description: The Denon DP-29F Belt Drive Turntable makes playing analog records simple thanks to its fully automatic operation. With a touch of a button the music starts playing and when the record's over the tonearm returns to its original position and the turntable stops. This makes sure you don't accidentally scratch your record.This turntable has a built-in RIAA phono equalizer, which allows you to connect it straight to an amp that doesn't have an equalizer.

fields.name: LENCO LS-100 Belt Drive Bluetooth Turntable - Brown Wood
fields.description: Play your record collection with the Lenco LS-100 Belt Drive Bluetooth Turntable. There's a pair of full-sized speakers included in the package, so you can fill your room with high-quality audio.The record player is equipped with auto-stop function, so your records will stop turning when they're over. Also, the hinged plastic cover protects your records from dust.

fields.name: Cup Pink Floyd - Prism
fields.description: These mugs are not suitable for the microwave or dishwasher

fields.name: Whats It Gonna Take
fields.description: What's It Gonna Take? is the 43rd studio album by Northern Irish singer-songwriter Van Morrison, released on 20 May 2022.

fields.name: The Ballad Of Darren
fields.description: The Ballad of Darren, the ninth album from Britpop pioneers Blur, catches four friends reconvening in their 50s to tackle daunting adult problems — the end of romance and the onset of middle age

fields.name: Raw Power
fields.description: Raw Power is the third studio album by American rock band the Stooges, released on February 7, 1973 by Columbia Records.

fields.name: Folk Singer
fields.description: Folk Singer is the fourth studio album by Muddy Waters, released in January 1964 by Chess Records. The album features Waters on acoustic guitar, backed by Willie Dixon on string bass, Clifton James on drums, and Buddy Guy on acoustic guitar. It is Waters's only all-acoustic album.

fields.name: Astral Weeks
fields.description: Astral Weeks is the second studio album by Northern Irish singer-songwriter Van Morrison. It was recorded at Century Sound Studios in New York during September and October 1968, and released in November of the same year by Warner Bros. Records

fields.name: The Gilded Palace Of Sin
fields.description: The Gilded Palace of Sin is the first album by the country rock group the Flying Burrito Brothers, released on February 6, 1969.

fields.name: Meddle
fields.description: Meddle is the sixth studio album by English rock band Pink Floyd, released by Harvest Records. The album was produced between the band's touring commitments, from January to August 1971 at a series of locations around London, including EMI Studios and Morgan Studios.

fields.name: Houses Of The Holy
fields.description: Houses of the Holy is the fifth studio album by the English rock band Led Zeppelin, released on 28 March 1973 by Atlantic Records. The album benefited from two band members installing studios at home, which allowed them to develop more sophisticated songs and arrangements and expand their musical style.

fields.name: Bad Brains
fields.description: Bad Brains are an American band formed in Washington, D.C., in 1976. They are widely regarded as pioneers of hardcore punk, though the band's members have objected to the use of this term to describe their music.

fields.name: Kid A
fields.description: Kid A is the fourth studio album by the English rock band Radiohead, released on 2 October 2000 by Parlophone. It was recorded with their producer, Nigel Godrich, in Paris, Copenhagen, Gloucestershire and Oxfordshire.

fields.name: Bangerz
fields.description: Bangerz is the fourth studio album by American singer Miley Cyrus, released on September 30, 2013, by RCA Records. It is her first body of original work since leaving Hollywood Records after her third studio album Can't Be Tamed and signing with RCA in early 2013

fields.name: After Hours
fields.description: After Hours is the fourth studio album by Canadian singer the Weeknd, released on March 20, 2020, by XO and Republic Records. Primarily produced by the Weeknd, it features a variety of producers, including DaHeala, Illangelo, Max Martin, Metro Boomin, and OPN, most of whom the Weeknd had worked with previously.

fields.name: Ephorize
fields.description: Ephorize is the third studio album by American rapper Cupcakke. It was self-released on January 5, 2018 via TuneCore

fields.description: Conductor: Paul Kuentz, Engineer: Hans-Peter Schweigmann, Harp: Nicanor Zabaleta, Orchestra: Orchestre de Chambre Paul Kuentz, Photography By: A. Soulet.

fields.name: Exodus

fields.name: No Fences
fields.description: No Fences is the second studio album by the American country music artist Garth Brooks. It was released on August 27, 1990, and reached No. 1 on Billboard's Top Country Albums chart.

fields.name: Golden Hour
fields.description: Kacey Musgraves' fourth studio album, Golden Hour, is a country pop album that explores themes of love, marriage, and happiness. The album features hit singles such as "Space Cowboy," "Slow Burn," and "Me!"

fields.name: Uprising
fields.description: Uprising is Bob Marley & The Wailers' ninth and final studio album. It was released just two months before Marley's death in 1981. The album features songs such as "Could You Be Loved," "Redemption Song," and "Zion Train."

fields.name: Singin' The Blues
fields.description: Singin' the Blues is the first LP album by American bluesman B.B. King, released in 1957 by the Bihari brothers on their Crown budget label. fields.name: Rum Sodomy And The Lash
fields.description: Rum Sodomy & the Lash is the second studio album by the London-based folk punk band The Pogues, released on 5 August 1985. The album reached number 13 on the UK charts. The track "A Pair of Brown Eyes", based on an older Irish tune, reached number 72 on the UK singles chart.

fields.name: Nevermind
fields.description: Nevermind is the second studio album by the American rock band Nirvana, released on September 24, 1991, by DGC Records. It was Nirvana's first release on a major label and the first to feature drummer Dave Grohl.
